@BlackRose so rather then starting with a idea and trying to find a project to fit it with this is what I tell people to do.
 Wall text warning...

Take 30 to 60 minutes in a quite room no distractions. A room that will inspire you. A attic,   grandads shop,a friend's home, a university or museums,  where ever you get inspired at. Set out an hour this week and just go tethered with a pen and paper and write down everything that pops in your head when you think about inventing something or building or making or DaVinci or any of that. Look around. You need to just write a list of 1 to 5 words per line just to capture the idea and move on to

the next idea. Don't think about the idea the purpose is to get as many thoughts down on paper as you can, not to write a story or a book.

Just make a list there is no reason you should have less then 1 project written down per minute spent. Don't matter how crazy. Or how small. Put them all down.

After words wait a day then go over that list and make some columns. Put a number in each one To 5.
How hard it is.
How interested you are in it.
How long it would take.
How much it would cost.
If there is anything else you can think of add that column there also.
Then place the numbers there.
5 would be the easiest, want to do it the most, cost the least, take the shortest time, ect.

Then go throughout your list and start scheduling them accordingly.
Maybe you want to start off with 2 easy sho

rt cheep ones you can bust out one each week end.
 
Then toss in one that realy interests you but is very hard and long and will take you two months..
